{"cursor":"5649","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n'Margaret J. Wheatley' (commonly 'Meg Wheatley') is a writer and management\nconsultant who studies organizational behavior. Her approach includes systems\nthinking, theories of change, chaos theory, leadership and the learning\norganization: particularly its capacity to self-organize. Her work is often\ncompared to that of Donella Meadows and Dee Hock. She describes her work as\nopposing \"highly controlled mechanistic systems that only create robotic\nbehaviors.\"\n","linknr":121,"url":"Margaret_Wheatley","recorded":1362476952,"links":12,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["American management consultants","American non-fiction writers","Harvard University alumni","Living people","New York University alumni","Brigham Young University faculty","Year of birth missing (living people)"],"headings":["Background","Current work and publications","Quotes","See also","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Management_consultant","Organizational_behavior","Systems_thinking","Change","Chaos_theory","Leadership","Learning_organization","Self-organize","Donella_Meadows","Dee_Hock","Mechanistic_paradigm","Peace_Corps","Harvard_University","New_York_University","Marriott_School_of_Management","Brigham_Young_University","The_Berkana_Institute","Myron_Kellner-Rogers","The_da_Vinci_Medallion","Fritjof_Capra","Systems_Thinking"]}